<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1325,559,1305]" pageId="12" pageNumber="63">
Meyrick described this species based on 
<specimenCount box="[740,898,559,585]" pageId="12" pageNumber="63" type="generic">31 specimens</specimenCount>
collected by Parish in 
<collectingRegion box="[1163,1228,559,585]" country="Peru" name="Lima" pageId="12" pageNumber="63">Lima</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1240,1294,559,585]" name="Peru" pageId="12" pageNumber="63">Peru</collectingCountry>
in 
<date box="[264,418,599,625]" pageId="12" pageNumber="63" value="1914-08">August 1914</date>
. Presently, there are 
<specimenCount box="[661,801,599,625]" pageId="12" pageNumber="63" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">14 syntypes</specimenCount>
in the BMNH, the location of the remainder of Meyrick’s original series is unknown. Meyrick ended his description by stating that this was “a variable species” without being more explicit. Six 
<typeStatus box="[972,1074,679,705]" pageId="12" pageNumber="63">syntypes</typeStatus>
(
<specimenCount box="[1094,1139,679,705]" pageId="12" pageNumber="63" type="male">3 ♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[1202,1246,679,705]" pageId="12" pageNumber="63" type="female">3 ♀</specimenCount>
) were examined and their genitalia dissected. I observed little variation in the 
<typeStatus box="[1144,1246,719,745]" pageId="12" pageNumber="63">syntypes</typeStatus>
that I examined. Considering Meyrick’s unconfirmed statement about intraspecific variability, the unknown location of half of the 
<typeStatus box="[696,801,799,825]" pageId="12" pageNumber="63">syntypes</typeStatus>
, and the close similarity between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1917" box="[1207,1323,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Coleophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intexta">
<emphasis box="[1207,1323,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="63">C. intexta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Landry" authorityYear="2006" box="[314,440,839,864]" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Coleophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darwini">
<emphasis box="[314,440,839,864]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="63">C. darwini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is advisable to fix Meyrick’s concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1917" box="[955,1070,839,864]" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Coleophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intexta">
<emphasis box="[955,1070,839,864]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="63">C. intexta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by designating a 
<typeStatus pageId="12" pageNumber="63">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
