<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1325,559,1305]" pageId="12" pageNumber="63">
<bibRefCitation author="Pastrana, J. A." box="[312,528,1159,1185]" pageId="12" pageNumber="63" pagination="89 - 101" refId="ref4750" refString="Pastrana, J. A. (1963) La familia Coleophoridae (Lep.) en la America Latina. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 26 [1962], 89 - 101." type="journal article" year="1963">Pastrana’s (1963)</bibRefCitation>
treatment of this species in his review of the Argentinian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1822" box="[264,404,1199,1224]" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Coleophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[264,404,1199,1224]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="63">Coleophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is essentially a Spanish translation of Meyrick’s description and is not accompanied by illustrations, suggesting that he did not examine specimens. I have not seen further specimens in collections. The host plant is unknown.
